caption.p:
Map showing locations in south‐western Australia of the six estuaries in which 
   Acanthopagrus butcheri was sampled by seine and gill nets in 2013–15. Freshwater discharge are provided in Figure 
   2 for these estuaries and the Blackwood River Estuary. Location of Beaufort Inlet, which acted as a surrogate for Wellstead Estuary for both discharge and used in the hydrological model, is also shown. Estuaries and ocean are shaded. 
   IO: intermittently‐open; 
   NC: normally‐closed; 
   PO: permanently‐open; 
   SO: seasonally‐open
